Let the number of red 4-door cars be $x$.  Since $\frac13$ of the cars are red, there are $\frac13\cdot 30 = 10$ red cars, so there are $10 -x$ red 2-door cars.  There are $(50\%)\cdot 30 = (0.5)(30) = 15$ cars that are 4-door cars, so $15-x$ of the 4-door cars are not red.  We then have the following Venn diagram:

[asy]
